      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structconn__mgr__conn__api_1ad2bb08d518e2f797002ca5257889a59e" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>void(*</type>
        <definition>void(* conn_mgr_conn_api::init) (struct conn_mgr_conn_binding *const binding)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(struct conn_mgr_conn_binding *const binding)</argsstring>
        <name>init</name>
        <qualifiedname>conn_mgr_conn_api::init</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Called once for each iface that has been bound to a connectivity implementation using this API. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Connectivity implementations should use this callback to perform any required per-bound-iface initialization.</para>
<para>Implementations may choose to gracefully handle invalid buffer lengths with partial writes, rather than raise errors, if deemed appropriate. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
